OL,3,CHilary Benn insists 'enduring' UK-US
OL,4,Crelationship despite Trump comments
OL,6,FThe Secretary of State has said the
OL,7,Frelationship between the UK and US
OL,8,Fgovernments will continue, despite
OL,9,Fangry comments from President Donald
OL,10,FTrump over the British response to the
OL,11,FMiddle East conflict.
OL,13,FHilary Benn MP was speaking ahead of
OL,14,FSt Patrick's Day celebrations at the
OL,15,FWhile House on Tuesday.
OL,17,FUS President Donald Trump has said he
OL,18,Fis "not happy" with Sir Keir Starmer
OL,19,Fafter the Prime Minister said he
OL,20,Fwanted a "viable" option to reopen the
OL,21,FStrait of Hormuz.
OL,26,@zD@DOUzD@NO]|D@JOU|D@QO]
